{# src/_includes/region/modules/microclimates.njk #}
  <h3>Microclimates That Matter</h3>

  {% set season = state.season or null %}
  {% set derived = season and season.derived or null %}
  {% set fallSpread = derived and derived.fallSpreadDays50 or null %}
  {% set frostFreeDays = derived and derived.frostFreeDays_p50 or null %}

  {% if not season %}
    <p class="small">Microclimate guidance isn’t available for this region yet.</p>

  {% else %}

    <p class="small" style="margin-top:-0.25rem;">
      Conditions often vary more within {{ state.name }} than most gardeners expect.
      Small differences in elevation, exposure, and surroundings can shift frost timing
      by days or even weeks.
    </p>

    <ul class="small" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">

      {# BIG VARIABILITY SIGNAL #}
      {% if fallSpread and fallSpread >= 28 %}
        <li>Frost timing varies widely across the region — colder pockets often form in low or exposed areas.</li>
      {% elif fallSpread and fallSpread >= 18 %}
        <li>Local conditions noticeably affect frost timing, especially between open and sheltered sites.</li>
      {% else %}
        <li>Most areas behave similarly, though small site differences still influence first frost timing.</li>
      {% endif %}

      {# UNIVERSAL MICROCLIMATE FACTORS #}
      <li>Urban and sheltered gardens usually stay warmer than rural or exposed locations.</li>
      <li>Cold air settles in low spots — slightly elevated beds often avoid the earliest frosts.</li>
      <li>South- and west-facing areas warm faster in spring and stay productive later into fall.</li>

      {# SHORT-SEASON EMPHASIS #}
      {% if frostFreeDays and frostFreeDays <= 115 %}
        <li>Choosing protected planting sites can significantly extend your usable growing window.</li>
      {% endif %}

    </ul>

    <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
      Tip: observe when nearby lawns frost over — your garden may behave differently than nearby weather stations.
    </p>

  {% endif %}
